description:
Support The Channel Here
https://www.evosounds.com

In this video, we're going to be going over the wavetable editor inside of Serum 2. I'll be giving you guys an overview of it and while we won't cover it to the extent of being a complete guide, we will cover as much as I understand so that you guys can start using it straight away. If you want a clear understanding of it, I suggest reading the manual, where there is some fancy lingo being used, which is obviously the correct terms; it just doesn't make sense unless you've heard how it changes the audio. I say you play with it, create your own wavetables as we do here, have fun with it, and then, if you seek to go further, do it.
